Small program to keep the cursor inside screen in dual-view Linux systems.
Designed for people who use slightly different window placement.

Not perfect -- uses about 2% of CPU all the time. Designed for my 2xfullhd displays
aligned like this (was too lazy to write code to fit for all alignments):

 __________
|          |
| Screen 1 |
|__________| __________
			|          |
			| Screen 2 |
			|__________|
